ramble /ˈræmbəl/

(rambling,rambled,rambles) 

1. N-COUNT A ramble is a long walk in the countryside. (乡间的) 漫步 

例： ...an hour's ramble through the woods. …1小时穿过树林的漫步。 

2. V-I If you ramble , you go on a long walk in the countryside. (在乡间) 漫步 

例： ...freedom to ramble across the rolling hills. …跨越起伏的丘陵漫步的自由。 

3. V-I If you say that a person rambles in their speech or writing, you mean they do not make much sense because they keep going off the subject in a confused way. 漫谈 

例： Sometimes she spoke sensibly; sometimes she rambled. 有时她说话很有道理；有时却漫无边际。

